“licence  to  operate  or  provide”  means  a  licence  to  operate  or 
provide  a  private  healthcare  facility  or  service  other  than  a  private 
medical clinic or private dental clinic granted under paragraph 19(a);

“licensee” means a person to whom a licence to operate or provide 
a  private  healthcare  facility  or  service  other  than  a  private  medical 
clinic or private dental clinic granted under paragraph 19(a);

“hospice  care  or  palliative  care”  means  care  of  a  terminally  ill 
person  that  addresses  the  physical,  psychological,  emotional  and 
social needs of the person or his family;

